// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - MM_Rogue_SL8-9_Task_01 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - Arbiter 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P2808787126" "Ah, {HeroName}, I'm glad you made it. I was informed ahead of time that you accepted our offer, though I do apologize that I could not inform you of what is happening beforehand."
// Answer Text :
"P514323127" "Not a problem. Let's get down to business."
// Page InformationPage1 Text :
"P1486177202" "A {Hero.gender=male man|woman} of business, just as I was told. <br><br>Very well. You are aware of the situation we have with our Bane Spiders? Some of them have been breaking free of our mental network and have gone rogue, hiding in the slums of the Isles."
// Answer Text :
"P2821837755" "Okay..."
// Page InformationPage2 Text :
"P2893062543" "For the most part, Westin Phipps has been able to track each of them down, though we have currently run into an...issue.<br><br>Part of the slums have become more...self-reliant lately. They aren't going to Haven House for food or supplies - they're actually able to survive on their own. Which would mean that we do not have an inside source on part of the slums. This is something that we can't let slide - not with the current issue at hand."
// Answer Text :
"P3925345011" "Still waiting for the part where I come in, Arbiter..."
// Page InformationPage3 Text :
"P1269874772" "Yes, of course.<br><br>We have taken over a Malta base within here.<br><br>You will pilot a Zeus Class Titan into the slums - the turrets around Grandville will fire blanks at you, of course. <br><br>Once you're in the designated section of the slums, you will unleash everything you have on the buildings within there. We've calculated the payload within the titan - it will be enough to destroy half of the apartments there, while severely damaging the others.<br><br>This will inflict many casualties...however the most important thing is that the people in these slums will no longer have enough to be self-reliant. They will be forced to go back to Haven House, where Westin Phipps will once again be able to get any information out of them.<br><br>In the end, an Arachnos patrol will arrive to take down the titan - at this point you will make your escape.<br><br>Any questions?"
// Answer Text :
"P3241642714" "...you want me to open fire on the homes of normal families?"
// Page Families Text :
"P1762262250" "Hrm...well, yes, granted there are probably several poor families living there.<br><br>However, the case of finding rogue Bane Spiders is more important. As well, it will bolster the people's faith that Arachnos is here to protect them...making it harder for the people of the slums to sympathize for these 'heroic' Bane Spiders who have broken free."
// Answer Text :
"P1680001931" "You can't be serious! This is attacking innocent civilians!"
// Page Innocent Text :
"P3438795195" "I was told you were someone who had no moral qualms, {HeroName}. Was I wrong?"
// Answer Text :
"P854104509" "You're right. But even I have a line, and this is it."
// Page Line Text :
"P2435867901" "This is most...troubling.<br><br>So are you going to turn down the job offer?"
// Answer Text :
"P2177249537" "I'm turning it down. I don't deal in slaughters, Becklo."
// Page Slaughters Text :
"P3194630206" "<color orange>Arbiter Becklo's hand rests on a shotgun at his side.</color><br><br>A shame. You leave me no choice but to put you down, {HeroName}. We can't have someone like you just going around with this information now, can we?"
// Answer Text :
"P1420564795" "Make one more move and you're going to regret it, Becklo."
// Page Regret Text :
"P747168121" "<color orange>Arbiter Becklo goes to pull out his shotgun - you quickly disable the man and knock him out with a powerful attack! You over hear his last words...</color><br><br>If you won't help us...then we'll just activate it...remotely...inside the warehouse...!"
// Answer Text :
"P1326795425" "I have a feeling this won't end well."
// Page ArbiterDestroyed Text :
"P3963908263" "<color orange>You look towards the warehouse.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P3898145311" "Close"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - BlastFurnace 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P1104773731" "<color orange>Blast Furnace glares at you from within his helmet, ready for a fight - though his armor is badly damaged, with smoke rising from the numerous cracks all over it - clearly he has just come from a fight.</color><br><br>I'll bring you in too, {HeroName}! Especially if you're working with Arachnos...prepare to be engulfed in the power of -"
// Answer Text :
"P4049792016" "Whoa whoa... easy there, tin man. I'm not with these guys."
// Page InformationPage1 Text :
"P1471454730" "<color orange>Blast Furnace pauses, letting out a pained groan.</color><br><br>Prove it!"
// Answer Text :
"P3514934997" "...look around. These Arachnos didn't defeat themselves, you know."
// Page InformationPage2 Text :
"P1665126599" "...fair enough. Urgh! <br><br><color orange>Blast Furnace slumps to the ground in a coughing fit.</color><br><br>Have...to stop Arachnos...!"
// Answer Text :
"P2709580891" "I took care of it. This one's on the house."
// Page InformationPage3 Text :
"P144450674" "You don't understand...! They have a plan B...!<br><br>They plan on...using the devices in that warehouse...to launch remote missiles on the slums...<br><br><color orange>Blast Furnace coughs for a few moments.</color><br><br>Was their...backup plan...in case the Titan was removed...and to...'silence'...whoever worked with them!"
// Answer Text :
"P839284578" "Hmph...should've known."
// Page Known Text :
"P1166063977" "<color orange>Blast Furnace struggles back up to his feet.</color><br><br>Out of my way...I'm going to burst in there...and stop whoever is behind this...!"
// Answer Text :
"P3872582550" "I hate to break it to you, but you're done for if you walk in there."
// Page Break Text :
"P2646186316" "Then who will stop Arachnos?!"
// Answer Text :
"P4288599237" "...look, alright, I'll make an exception and bail you all out of this one."
// Page Exception Text :
"P2271000304" "You...? You would actually do this for free?"
// Answer Text :
"P1114168212" "Only because of how ridiculous this situation is. Got it?"
// Page Gotit Text :
"P1394946429" "I understand. I shall patrol the skies out here and ensure no Arachnos attempt to ambush you from within."
// Answer Text :
"P2204076300" "Yeah, I'm sure you'll be a big help."
// Page Sarcasm Text :
"P1704174930" "<color orange>Blast Furnace turns and flies off to patrol the skies, leaving you to deal with Arachnos.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P980018338" "Not even a thank you. Unbelievable."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - BlastFurnace2 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P3212607808" "<color orange>Blast Furnace seems to have patched himself up since your last encounter with him - just in time to see you finish off everything.</color><br><br>I must admit that you did an admirable job here, {HeroName}. I didn't think that someone like...<i>you</i>...could pull this off."
// Answer Text :
"P1333761176" "Thanks for the vote of confidence, Blast Furnace."
// Page InformationPage1 Text :
"P1846523855" "Of course.<br><br>I am sure now, however, that you will be doing what is right and coming along with me - to turn yourself in to the authorities in Paragon."
// Answer Text :
"P1943464648" "...what?"
// Page InformationPage2 Text :
"P2557665799" "For all the crimes you've comitted, of course.<br><br>Did you think I'm just going to LET you get away now that I have you here?<br><br>You can make this easier, however, by just coming along quietly."
// Answer Text :
"P3986364367" "You're out of your mind if you think I'm letting you arrest me!"
// Page InformationPage3 Text :
"P3325961809" "<color orange>Spits of fire shoot out from Blast Furnace's helm.</color><br><br>So, your case of charity has ended, I see."
// Answer Text :
"P2162084677" "It never included being dragged to prison by you."
// Page Dragged Text :
"P775132932" "Then plans can be changed, {HeroName}!"
// Answer Text :
"P2594106647" "We'll see about that!"
// Page BlastFurnaceBetrayal Text :
"P3883484756" ""<color orange>Blast Furnace lunges at you.</color>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P4105258378" "You put out a call to some of your reliable contacts to find out everything you can about this Arbiter Becklo.<br><br>Soon enough you have all the information you need, including where he is at this very moment - Warburg. Becklo is a respected Arbiter, known for his extreme loyalty to Arachnos (as all Arbiters are) as well as being Arbiter Daos's 'go to' person for solving conflicts between the patrons - in other words, a man who has a reputation within Arachnos for being trustworthy. Of course, this is being trustworthy...<i>within Arachnos</i>...so how much that actually means is debatable.<br><br>At any case, even if it is a trap, it would be easy enough to get out of it from within Warburg - what do you have to lose?"
// AcceptString :
"P4066896837" "Rendezvous with Arbiter Becklo!"
// SendOffString :
"P3783569726" "You'll have to head towards the Arachnos Flyer within St. Martial, where Becklo assured you that a pilot would be waiting to personally fly you out towards their location within Warburg. Then it's just a matter of making the deal and going through with it - nothing that should be too difficult for you."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P2469781874" "Make a deal with Arachnos!"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P2120490657" "Worse case scenario, they betray you, you beat them down, then sell their equipment on the black market."
// TaskTitle :
"P4153642505" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Easy Job, Easy Money!</color></span></scale></font>"
// TaskSubTitle :
"P292316059" "<span align=center><color orange><i>Rogue Morality Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P1447019499" "You arrive at the Arachnos site in Warburg, noticing that Arachnos has their full guard up, just in case any other supers try to break into this warehouse."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P1024025774" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Easy Job, Easy Money!</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color orange><i>Morality Mission</i></color></span><br><br>Despite your actions against Arbiter Becklo, Arachnos has backed away from any further conflict on the matter - most likely because they cannot risk the plan they had to be revealed, as it would give away Westin Phipps and his entire operation.<br><br>You showed Arachnos, though, that you are willing to do a job for the right price - but even someone like yourself has a line of what is acceptable.<br><br>When someone crosses that line, you're sure to be there to put them in their place."

